{"abstract":[{"text":"An encoder which converts ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Encodable"},{"text":" values into XML.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/sdgxml\/xml\/encoder"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Encoder","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"struct","extendedModule":"SDGXML","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:6SDGXML3XMLO7EncoderV","roleHeading":"Structure","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Encoder","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"SDGXML"}],"title":"XML.Encoder"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SDGXML\/documentation\/SDGXML\/XML\/Encoder"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SDGXML\/documentation\/SDGXML","doc:\/\/SDGXML\/documentation\/SDGXML\/XML"]]},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Encoder"}],"platforms":["Linux"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Several related types can be used to customize the XML representation. All of them are demonstrated in the example that follows."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"@XML.Attribute","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property wrapper can be applied to ","type":"text"},{"code":"LosslessStringConvertible","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" properties to make them encode as an attributes instead of as child elements.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"XML.Element","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instances are encoded vertabim, so custom XML can be assembled and fed to the encoder.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"CustomXMLRepresentable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" protocol provide additional customization:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It can be used to provide a DTD."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It can request a default element name be used whenever its name is not already constrained by a coding key. This occurs for the root element of the document, and for elements which occur in an unkeyed container, such as array elements.","type":"text"}]}]}]}]}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct Document: Codable, CustomXMLRepresentable {","","  var dtd: XML.DTD? {  \/\/ CustomXMLRepresentable","    return .system(\"file:\/\/localhost\/Some\/File.dtd\")","  }","","  var defaultElementName: StrictString? {  \/\/ CustomXMLRepresentable","    return \"document\"","  }","","  var basicChildElement: String = \"basic child element\"","","  @XML.Attribute var attribute: String = \"attribute\"","","  struct CustomChild: Codable {","    init() {}","    func encode(to encoder: Encoder) throws {","      var container = encoder.singleValueContainer()","      try container.encode(","        XML.Element(","          name: \"custom\",","          content: [","            .characterData(\"A mix of text and \"),","            .element(XML.Element(name: \"elements\")),","            .characterData(\".\"),","          ]","        )","      )","    }","    init(from decoder: Decoder) throws {","      let container = try decoder.singleValueContainer()","      let element = try container.decode(XML.Element.self)","      XCTAssertEqual(element.name, \"custom\")","      XCTAssertEqual(element.content.first?.description, \"A mix of text and \")","    }","  }","  var custom: CustomChild = CustomChild()","","  struct UnnamedChild: Codable {","    init() {}","  }","  var unnamedArray: [UnnamedChild] = [UnnamedChild(), UnnamedChild(), UnnamedChild()]","","  struct NamedChild: Codable, CustomXMLRepresentable {","    var defaultElementName: StrictString? {","      return \"named\"","    }","  }","  var namedArray: [NamedChild] = [NamedChild(), NamedChild(), NamedChild()]","}","","let encoder = XML.Encoder()","let xml = try encoder.encodeToSource(Document())","XCTAssertEqual(","  xml,","  [","    \"<?xml version=\\u{22}1.1\\u{22} encoding=\\u{22}UTF\\u{2D}8\\u{22}?>\",","    \"<!DOCTYPE document SYSTEM \\u{22}file:\/\/localhost\/Some\/File.dtd\\u{22}>\",","    \"<document attribute=\\u{22}attribute\\u{22}>\",","    \" <basicChildElement>basic child element<\/basicChildElement>\",","    \" <custom>A mix of text and <elements\/>.<\/custom>\",","    \" <namedArray>\",","    \"  <named\/>\",","    \"  <named\/>\",","    \"  <named\/>\",","    \" <\/namedArray>\",","    \" <unnamedArray>\",","    \"  <UnnamedChild\/>\",","    \"  <UnnamedChild\/>\",","    \"  <UnnamedChild\/>\",","    \" <\/unnamedArray>\",","    \"<\/document>\",","  ].joined(separator: \"\\n\")",")"]}],"kind":"content"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SDGXML\/documentation\/SDGXML\/XML\/Encoder\/init(userInformation:)"],"title":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SDGXML\/documentation\/SDGXML\/XML\/Encoder\/userInformation"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SDGXML\/documentation\/SDGXML\/XML\/Encoder\/encode(_:)","doc:\/\/SDGXML\/documentation\/SDGXML\/XML\/Encoder\/encodeToSource(_:)"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://SDGXML/documentation/SDGXML/XML/Encoder/encode(_:)":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/sdgxml\/xml\/encoder\/encode(_:)","title":"encode(_:)","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Encodes a top‐level value as XML data."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"encode","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Value","kind":"generic